I don't usually give such low reviews but this by far is the worst Dunkin Donuts on the planet. The absolute worst! The business location itself is awful, being the size of a shoe box. The hiring manager is garbage because he/she/they don't seem to know how to hire people who actually know how to provide appropriate customer service in the morning. Very rarely do I ever see the customers mouthing off or being rude to the staff, and if that were the case then I could understand why they wouldn't be pleasant, but the staff is consistently rude to the customers; to the point of ignoring people and have even witnessed a staff throw someone's food AT them. In my experience, no matter how often I visit the establishment, it always takes a ridiculous amount of time to receive my food order, and there is always an issue, whether they forget to add something to the order, put the wrong ingredient, or forget to make something that I had ordered. Maybe it is because there isn't a different location in the area, but I have no idea how this place stays in business. The only silver lining I can think of is that I have never gotten food poisoning from eating at this specific specific location. I recommend just ordering from a different Dunkin through a food delivery app.

The King of Craft Donuts  Doughnut  is one of a kind. It's special in almost every single way and it made me a very happy customer. I traveled to New York to watch the US Open. Since I was there, I had to try the best spot this city had to offer. I arrived at the door and I couldn't just get two donuts for one sitting. I had to get four.  P  All of these donuts blew my mind. The quality of ingredients, texture, and overall taste of the donuts exceeded my expectations. The Peanut Butter & Blackberry Jam donut took me by surprise. I really wasn't looking forward to it because I had too many of these sandwiches in high school. However, when seeking my teeth into the nutty and sweet combo, I realized how much these two ingredients are meant to be together. The texture of the donut was just delightfully soft. The nuts gave it a perfect crunch while the sweet layer of jam smoothed out the taste. I've had a couple of Crème Brulee donuts before but the one at Doughnut Plant is the best. The hard caramel on top gave it that candy like break while the custard on the inside was just leveled with the right amount of sweetness. The Brooklyn Blackout is a chocolate lover's dream. It's a chocolate cake donut, with chocolate fudge, frosted with chocolate icing, and topped with chocolate crumbs. a Green Tea was fantastic as well. Extraordinary flavors of green tea made this cake donut wonderful to eat.  The craft donut shop really impressed me with the quality and variety. They had so many other options I wanted to try like Definitely a must visit spot for donut fanatics. I know there are more donut spots in NY but I'll definitely be back here soon enough.  One thing I do have to mention is that they don't serve regular donuts like maple or apple fritter.
